[center][size=6][b]ItemMagnet[/b][/size]
[size=4]Tiered item magnets with redstone fuel, smart filters, visible pull physics, and claim-aware protection.[/size][/center]

[hr][/hr]

ItemMagnet is a [b]Paper[/b] plugin built for survival SMPs. Pull dropped loot with [b]line-of-sight physics[/b] — items slide around corners and stop at walls instead of phasing through blocks. Fuel resonators with redstone, respect land claims, and tune everything from an in-game config GUI or YAML.

[hr][/hr]

[size=5][b]Why ItemMagnet?[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]Visible physics[/b] — step-based pull with line-of-sight; no wall clipping
[*][b]Claim-aware[/b] — Lands, WorldGuard, Towny, GriefPrevention, Residence, PlotSquared, SuperiorSkyblock2
[*][b]Smart filters[/b] — server + personal blacklists, Minecraft tag rules, tier whitelists, presets with preview/confirm
[*][b]Redstone fuel loop[/b] — dust and blocks recharge the magnet; redstone blocks trigger a radius boost
[*][b]Admin-friendly[/b] — [icode]/itemmagnet config[/icode] GUI, hot reload, presets, LuckPerms-ready permissions
[*][b]Production storage[/b] — player filters in YAML, SQLite, or MySQL
[/list]

[size=5][b]Gameplay[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Three configurable tiers (Fragment, Survey, Anchor) with recipes and unlock gates
[*]Hold modes: main hand, hotbar, or inventory
[*]Optional XP orb pulling
[*]Live lore: charge, boost, and current pull radius
[*]Sneak + right-click fuel or auto-absorb redstone drops
[/list]

[size=5][b]Filters[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Server material + tag blacklist (config + admin GUI)
[*]Personal filter GUI — [icode]/itemmagnet filter[/icode]
[*]Built-in presets (mining, farming, mob-drops, keep-valuables) with merge preview
[*][icode]/itemmagnet filter clear[/icode] and import commands
[*]YAML, SQLite, or MySQL storage for player filter data
[/list]

[size=5][b]Integrations (optional)[/b][/size]
Lands · WorldGuard · Towny · GriefPrevention · Residence · PlotSquared · SuperiorSkyblock2 · CMI · LuckPerms · mcMMO · Quests · PlaceholderAPI · Developer API

[hr][/hr]

[size=5][b]Requirements[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Paper [b]1.21.1+[/b] (Java [b]21+[/b])
[*]Tested on Paper 1.21.1, 1.21.4, 26.1
[*]Not supported: Spigot, CraftBukkit, Folia
[/list]

[size=5][b]Quick start[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Drop the JAR in [icode]plugins/[/icode] and restart
[*][icode]/itemmagnet give <player> fragment 500[/icode]
[*]Hold the magnet, sneak + right-click with redstone dust to fuel
[*]Drop items nearby — they pull toward you with visible motion
[/list]

